<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Best Scrabble Words With W — Strategy & High Scorers</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">W is one of Scrabble's most underrated tiles. Worth 4 points with 2 in the bag, it combines with almost every vowel and forms powerful digraphs (WH, WR) that start hundreds of common words. Unlike V, W happily ends words (BOW, DEW, RAW) giving you flexibility in tight board positions.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">W Tile at a Glance</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tile value</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tiles in bag</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">WH WR OW AW</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Key combos</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Top Scoring W Words</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
  <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
    <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
      <tr>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Word</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Points</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Length</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Notes</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">WHIZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">19</td><td class="px-4 py-3">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3">W(4)+H(4)+Z(10)</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">WAX</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3">W(4)+X(8) power pair</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">WAXWORK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">24</td><td class="px-4 py-3">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Bingo candidate</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">WHACK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">W(4)+H(4)+K(5)+C(3)</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">WHELK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">W(4)+H(4)+K(5)</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">WHIFF</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">W(4)+H(4)+FF(8)</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">HAWK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3">H(4)+W(4)+K(5)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">W-Ending Words (Board Savers)</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JAW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">YEW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VOW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DEW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">COW</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">8 pts</span></span>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">W Tile Strategy</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">WH is your opening gambit:</span> WHIZ, WHACK, WHALE, WHERE — WH words dominate high-scoring plays. When you draw W, immediately check if H is available for the WH combo.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">W ends words unlike V:</span> This is W's biggest advantage over V. Words ending in OW, AW, EW give you flexibility to play W at the board edge or in parallel positions where V would be stuck.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Pair with premium tiles:</span> W+Z (WHIZ=19), W+X (WAX=13), W+K (HAWK=14), W+J (JAW=13). Always look for these combinations before settling for a basic W play.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">W Combo Patterns</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">W's biggest strength over V is <span class="text-white font-medium">positional flexibility</span>. W starts words (WAS, WHACK), ends words (BOW, DEW, JAW), and sits in the middle (AWED, OWES, TOWN). This means W almost never gets stuck on your rack.</p>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">✓ W is flexible (unlike V)</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">W starts words, ends words, and appears mid-word. It pairs with all 5 vowels and forms useful digraphs with H and R.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
    <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">✗ V is restricted</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">V rarely ends words, almost always needs a vowel adjacent, and has fewer 2-letter options. W is the superior 4-point tile.</p>
  </div>
</div>

